## Overview

A workspace in Graphium AI is the top-level organizational container for your vaults, data, and team members. If your account belongs to multiple workspaces — for example, separate workspaces for different practices or facilities — you can identify your active workspace, view all available workspaces, and switch between them at any time from the navigation bar.

---

## The Workspace Indicator

The workspace indicator appears in the **top-left corner of the navigation bar**, immediately to the right of the Graphium logo. It consists of:

- A **colored square icon** displaying the workspace's two-letter abbreviation (e.g., **UA** for Urban Anesthesia)
- The **full workspace name** in white text
- A **chevron arrow (∨)** indicating the name is clickable
- A **gear icon (⚙)** to the right for accessing workspace settings

The color of the icon is unique to each workspace, making it easy to identify your active workspace at a glance.

