## Viewing Your Available Workspaces

1. From any page in Graphium AI, click the **workspace name** or **chevron arrow (∨)** in the top-left of the navigation bar.

2. The dropdown lists all workspaces available to your account, each showing a colored icon, full workspace name, and your currently active workspace highlighted at the top.

3. A **"Manage workspaces"** button appears at the bottom of the list.

4. To close without switching, press **Escape** or click anywhere outside the dropdown.

---

## Switching Workspaces

1. Open the workspace switcher by clicking the workspace name or chevron arrow (∨).

2. Click the name of the workspace you want to switch to.

3. The page refreshes and the nav bar updates to the new workspace's icon and name.

When you switch, the dashboard reloads showing only that workspace's vaults. Switching does **not** log you out, affect your session, delete any data, or change your user role. Roles are set per workspace.

> **Note:** Any user belonging to more than one workspace can switch freely — no special role is required. Creating or deactivating workspaces is restricted to **Workspace Owners**.

---

## The Manage Workspaces Page

Clicking **Manage workspaces** at the bottom of the dropdown opens a full workspace management page showing all your workspaces, an **"Add a workspace"** button (Workspace Owners only), and a **"Switch to this workspace"** button for every workspace other than your current one.

---

## Troubleshooting

| Issue | Likely Cause | What to Do |
|-------|-------------|------------|
| Workspace indicator is not visible | Navigation bar failed to load | Refresh the page; check your internet connection |
| Workspace shown is not the one I expected | You may be in a different workspace | Click the indicator to open the switcher and select the correct workspace |
| A workspace I don't recognize is shown | Account was added to a workspace by an administrator | Contact your workspace administrator |
| Only one workspace appears in the dropdown | Account may only belong to one workspace | Contact your administrator if you believe you need access to additional workspaces |
| The workspace I need is not in the list | You haven't been added to that workspace yet | Contact your administrator to request access |
| Switcher does not respond when clicked | Page or browser issue | Refresh the page and try again |
| Dashboard shows "No vaults yet" after switching | The selected workspace has no vaults | Expected for a new workspace — create a vault from this screen |
| Accidentally switched to the wrong workspace | — | Open the switcher again and click the correct workspace |

